  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is legally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legitimate by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific definitions vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Concealing the source of funds through complex transactions\n3. Integration - Making the funds appear legal and usable\n\nLegal definitions typically require:\n- Intentional concealment of funds from illegal activities\n- Knowledge that money originates from criminal sources\n- Deliberate attempts to disguise the money's origin\n- Transactions designed to hide the trail of illegal funds\n\nSpecific legal elements can include:\n- Transferring funds to hide criminal proceeds\n- Structuring financial transactions to avoid reporting requirements\n- Using legitimate businesses to mask illegal income\n- Creating complex financial instruments to obscure money's source\n\nPenalties often include:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nThe specific legal definition and penalties vary between countries and jurisdictions.",
